HEADWORD: horsebrier
<hw>horsebrier</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a very prickly woody vine
(<spn>Smilax rotundifolia</spn>) of eastern U. S. growing in tangled
masses having tough round stems with shiny leathery leaves and small
greenish flowers followed by clusters of inedible shiny black
berries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bullbrier, greenbrier, catbrier, brier, briar,
<spn>Smilax rotundifolia</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

